This paper deals with computer vision techniques for modifying facial expressions in videos, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also uses generative adversarial networks (GANs) to generate new facial expressions, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses unsupervised learning techniques for training the model, which is a common topic in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with the synthesis of photorealistic video frames, which is a topic in computer graphics (cs.GR).
